'''Midnight Madness''' was an event held across the United States at midnight, [[Wikipedia:April 2|April 2]], [[2005]], in which [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] toys and merchandise were officially released. Vendors that participated in Midnight Madness included [[Wikipedia:Wal-Mart|Wal-Mart]], [[Wikipedia:Target Inc.|Target]] and [[Wikipedia:Toys R Us|Toys R Us]].

Toys R Us held a similar midnight event for the [[2008]] release of the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars'' movie]]. In addition to the new [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] and [[Star Wars: The Legacy Collection|The Legacy Collection]] lines, the major items were the Big [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] (BMF) and the large [[All Terrain Tactical Enforcer/Legends|AT-TE]] vehicles.<ref>{{SWArchive|url=vault/collecting/f20080701.html|text=''Clone Wars'' Coming Soon to Toys "R" Us}}</ref>

"Midnight Madness" can also refer to the midnight premiere of a ''Star Wars'' movie. Many fans dress up as characters from the saga, most choosing [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] or [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], such as [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], and will wait in a line for over a day, if not longer. The advent of online ticket purchasing has reduced the number of people who wait in line to get a ticket, but rather to get a good seat.

